crowdsourced_yara_results.description: This signature detects the presence of a number of Windows API functionality often seen within embedded executables. When this signature alerts on an executable, it is not an indication of malicious behavior. However, if seen firing in other file types, deeper investigation may be warranted.

threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This is a Golang-based Remote Access Trojan (RAT). It establishes command and control (C2) communication using WebSockets, likely connecting to 'winfoacacorp.com'. The malware uses DNS-over-HTTPS (DoH) to public resolvers like '8.8.8.8' to hide its C2 resolution. Key malicious behaviors include providing a remote interactive shell, evidenced by the use of '/bin/sh' and pty-related libraries ('github.com/creack/pty'), file system browsing and transfer capabilities, and the ability to function as a SOCKS proxy.
